Rating: 4
My husband loves chicken marsala so I thought I'd give this recipe a go. After reading reviews, I also added garlic to the shallots, replaced the heavy cream with half and half and replaced some of the butter with vegetable oil. The dish turned out fantastic...still rich, but not over-the-top heavy. Because some reviewers complained about the sauce being too thin, I floured the chicken breasts twice -- I first salt/peppered the breasts, dredged them in flour, let them sit while I prepped the other ingredients. Right before I put them in the pan, I dredged them again. That left enough flour in the pan so that the sauce came out a nice consistency. Finally, I use "Better than Bouillon" reduce sodium chicken broth which is a concentrate so rather than make the full amount of broth and reduce it on the stovetop, I just dissolved a little more than 1 tsp of the bouillon in 3/4 cup of boiling water. Great time saver and they have the best store bought broth out there.

