Rating: 4
Loved this but trying to cook the chicken scallopines in the pan was a bit of a disaster. The first one was perfect but as the pan got hotter my butter was burning pretty quickly, even with the added olive oil. So I had lots of black flecks in the sauce and the last few pieces of chicken looked a bit Cajun-style! And it was a hassle wiping it out and adding olive oil and butter over and over again. I'd recommend just using the oil and pulling them out once both sides are a nice golden yellow, then put them all in the oven at the same time to finish them (7-8 minutes). The sauce also took longer to reduce than I expected, and was a little runnier than I would have liked. Perhaps add a bit less cream or a bit of cornstarch. I added two cloves of minced garlic to the shallot mix as another reviewer suggested. Also, you can easily double the amount of sage, and sprinkle some on the chicken before you flour them for a little extra oomph. Reduce the stock and make the mushrooms ahead of time and then set them aside to free up one of your burners for making pasta.

