Rating: 4
Here were the changes I made: Chicken Thighs (bone-in and with skin) not breasts. Port Wine, not Marsala. Small onion and 3 garlic cloves, not shallots. Did not reduce chicken broth. Only used a couple Tablespoons of cream. Here is how I made it: Heated oil in a dutch oven. Dredged thighs, browned on both sides, set aside. Sauteed onions and mushrooms in same dutch oven, cooked until liquid was almost gone. Added garlic and sage. After a few minutes, add broth and wine. Add browned thighs, cover loosely and simmer 30 min. Remove chicken, turn up heat and reduce sauce a bit. Finish with a couple of Tablespoons of heavy cream. YUM. I served over noodles. The sauce is fan-tastic!

