I had attempted Chicken Marsala once before and the chicken was tough. This recipe was fantastic! The only thing I did differently (besides using half and half instead of cream)was change up the order of the recipe so I could use just one pot. I first browned the chicken in my Le Creuset, removed it and set it aside. Then I added more butter and cooked the shallots and mushrooms, etc. Then I deglased the pan with the mushrooms still it it. I then added the chicken back in and covered and simmered for about 20 minutes. This let the chicken become extra tender. This might be the first time I've made anything that was better than a restaurant.

