A keeper & new favorite!! I made this recipe for a dinner party of seven last night and it was a huge hit. I read a number of the reviews and tweaked the recipe a bit&. I used a mix of mushrooms and used more than called for but not quite double. And be prepared to spend a little more time to cook off the liquid. I also used sweet marsala and IMO this is a key change. For the 8 servings I was making I used 1 ¾ cups (called for one). And when it came time to add it to the skillet I let it reduce just a bit to get some of that jammy quality everyone loves. Even doing that I think the sauce needs a few more minutes to thicken up. Its a personal preference, but I prefer mine on the thicker side. I didnt have the time to let it come together on its own so I sprinkled a bit of cornstarch (like other viewers) and PERFECTO! And I almost forgot the fresh sage. I stirred it in right before serving and it was another lovely dimension of flavor. Ive made a note to always do it at the last minute. And I skipped the lemon this time. I dont think it was missed. I served this with angel hair pasta, asparagus and garlic bread. Next time Ill use chicken strips or chunks to save effort and cooking time. And I may double the sauce and see how well it freezes& Thanks to all the reviewers of this recipe! And if youre reading this and debating if its worth the effort& it most certainly is!

