To Samantha 1824, The 3 reasons it would have curdled are, your cream was too old, the lemon juice itself reacting to the cream, or possibly the utensils you were using were unclean and had traces of acid or tannin. If you keep whisking sometimes it will come together, but once it separates it's kind of done. I am going to make this recipe, but since no one else seems to have mentioned the same issue, did you follow the recipe in the order it appears? Otherwise, I don't know and I cook and bake daily. Perhaps you put the lemon in too soon? I'm trying this tomorrow, we shall see

