Rating: 4
This recipe is absolutely divine. I make the full marsala recipe for only two chicken breasts (skinless, boneless) and always get a loaf of moist focaccia to soak up anything left on the plate. A few notes: I only use one tablespoon of shallot, 1/2 cup of cream, and I don't add the sage or lemon juice at the end (I usually forget, but it's never suffered for lack of either). I use regular-sodium chicken broth and the same amount of salt and pepper - then reduce the whole sauce at the end until it has a creamy thick consistency. Definitely double the recipe if you're trying to feed four people; I think the key to success with this dish is waiting for the sauce to reduce so the flavors condense and come together - don't make my initial mistake of adding more cream to make the sauce creamy, just wait for it to boil down and get thicker on its own.

