When my husband first suggested I put Chicken Marsala on the menu, I must admit my initial reaction was meh. It just struck me as one of those dishes you end up ordering at a sub-par restaurant because it might be the only thing the kitchen wont mess up too much. Even then, too many places overcook the chicken and the sauce leaves a whole lot to be desired. But thinking that I couldnt do any worse, I decided to give it a go (but with some reservations). With our first bites, there was absolute dead quiet. And then we looked at each other and I said, WOW  this is good. I mean, beyond good. This is incredibly, wonderfully good! WOW! The chicken was cooked just right  still juicy and oh-so-tender. But the sauce, the sauce was out of this world. I would have this sauce every day if it were possible. Its that great. My husband was only able to nod in agreement, because he was too busy scarfing down everything on his plate. There were instant regrets that I hadnt made the full recipe so we could have it again as leftovers. I will never think meh again when the subject of Chicken Marsala comes up. Really, if youve never tried making this dish, please do. Become one of the believers. For my full review, visit my blog at http://wrighttable.blogspot.com/.

