Rating: 4
Is your pan too hot? Try lowering the heat a bit. If you still have the blackened bits, remove the chicken from the pan and return the pan to the burner. Pour in some chicken broth or wine and scrape the bottom with a wooden spoon. Rinse out the pan and you should get rid of the black bits. Now you can proceed with the recipe. Hope this helps.

