This is solid and pretty easy dish to make. A few things to keep it simple are to make the broth reduction and mushroom mixture ahead of time. Buy the already thin sliced chicken breast. (To reduce broth or anything quickly use a wider pot/pan. More surface area means equals quicker reuction.) Also don't buy the cheap Marsla "cooking wine" you find in the grocery and splurge ($10) for the the stuff you buy in the wine or liqure store.

