Rating: 4
After reading the chef's comments, (about not enough sauce) I made these changes. I doubled the stock and reduced it about 30 minutes. I followed the rest of the sauce recipe so I was left with a thin sauce. I took 2 Tablespoons of butter and heated it and whisked in 2 Tablespoons of flour to make a roux. Cooked it 2 minutes, then added it to the sauce and cooked for 4 more minutes. I don't like a really heavy, creamy sauce, so it was lighter, and since some chef's said there wasn't enough sauce for the dish, this solved the problem. I was pleased with the outcome making the sauce this way. By the way you can cook the chicken and make the sauce seperately the day before then heat the sauce and pour over heated chicken on the say of the party.

